```java
// Array (fixed size)
int[] arr = new int[5];         // {0,0,0,0,0}
int[] arr = {1, 2, 3};
arr.length                       // 3 (field, not method!)

// ArrayList (dynamic, objects only)
import java.util.ArrayList;
ArrayList<Integer> list = new ArrayList<>();
list.add(42);           // append
list.add(0, 42);        // insert at index 0
list.get(i);            // access
list.set(i, val);       // update
list.remove(i);         // remove by index
list.size();            // length
```

```java
// For-each loop (read-only)
for (int x : arr) { ... }

// Traditional for loop
for (int i = 0; i < arr.length; i++) { ... }

// While / do-while
while (condition) { ... }
do { ... } while (condition);
```

**Short-circuit evaluation:** `&&` and `||` stop early when result is known.

```java
public class Animal {
    private String name;
    public Animal(String name) { this.name = name; }
    public String getName() { return name; }
    public String toString() { return "Animal: " + name; }
}

public class Dog extends Animal {
    public Dog(String name) { super(name); }
    @Override
    public String toString() { return "Dog: " + getName(); }
}
```

`super(...)` — call parent constructor (must be first line)

`instanceof` — check type at runtime
